title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\InstantiateInlineWorkflowTemplateRequest
name: InstantiateInlineWorkflowTemplateRequest
description:
A request to instantiate an inline workflow template.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.InstantiateInlineWorkflowTemplateRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The resource name of the region or location, as described in https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/resource_names. For projects.regions.workflowTemplates,instantiateinline, the resource name of the region has the following format: projects/{project_id}/regions/{region} For projects.locations.workflowTemplates.instantiateinline, the resource name of the location has the following format: projects/{project_id}/locations/{location}

params.name: data.request_id
params.description: Optional. A tag that prevents multiple concurrent workflow instances with the same tag from running. This mitigates risk of concurrent instances started due to retries. It is recommended to always set this value to a UUID. The tag must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). The maximum length is 40 characters.

methods.name: getRequestId
methods.description:
Optional. A tag that prevents multiple concurrent workflow instances with the same tag from running. This mitigates risk of concurrent instances started due to retries.

It is recommended to always set this value to a UUID. The tag must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). The maximum length is 40 characters.
